notes.text: a. Day -28 Screening
b. Specific visits for responders or specific day markers
c. Informed consent must be obtained before any study-specific procedures
d. C-SSRS, SBQ-R, and PHQ-8 are suicidality and mood assessments
e. Disease history includes Atopic Dermatitis specific details
f. Physical exams (Complete vs Targeted)
g. Vital signs include blood pressure, pulse, respiratory rate, and temperature
h. Laboratory assessments require specific fasting or conditions
i. Hematology includes CBC and differentials
j. Coagulation panel includes APTT, PT/INR
k. Serum chemistry includes standard metabolic panel
l. Urinalysis includes dipstick and microscopy if needed
m. Lipid panel requires 8-hour fasting
n. Pregnancy testing for females of childbearing potential
o. Urine pregnancy test conducted at site
p. HIV, Hepatitis, and Viral screening requirements
u. PK sampling timing relative to dose
v. Investigational Treatment Administration details
w. Eligibility for extension study B7451015
x. NRS assessed via eDiary
y. DLQI/CDLQI age-specific versions
z. PSAAD daily completion requirements
aa. EQ-5D age-specific versions
bb. SF-36v2 for adults only
cc. FACIT-F age-specific versions
ee. Flare assessment criteria
ff. Contraception check for relevant subjects
gg. Baseline viral screen samples
